        <NCI_PT rdf:datatype="&xsd;string">Conductive Hearing Loss</NCI_PT>
        <NCI_Definition rdf:datatype="&xsd;string">Hearing loss caused by a problem in the outer ear or middle ear. Conductive losses usually affect all frequencies to the same degree. These losses are not usually severe.</NCI_Definition>
