        <NCI_Definition rdf:datatype="&xsd;string">A malformation in the lung that is present at birth. Representative examples include pulmonary hypoplasia, pulmonary agenesis, congenital lobar emphysema, and alveolar capillary dysplasia.</NCI_Definition>
