        <NCI_Definition rdf:datatype="&xsd;string">A rare syndrome characterized by congenital abnormalities caused by fetal exposure to the administration of warfarin to the mother during pregnancy. The congenital abnormalities include nasal bridge depression, nasal bones hypoplasia, microcephaly, congenital heart disorders, and brachydactyly.</NCI_Definition>
        <ID rdf:datatype="&xsd;string">C98906</ID>
        <SYN rdf:datatype="&xsd;string">Fetal Coumadin Syndrome</SYN>
