        <SYN rdf:datatype="&xsd;string"></SYN>
        <NCI_Definition rdf:datatype="&xsd;string">An extremely rare autosomal recessive inherited disorder caused by mutations in the UMPS gene. It is characterized by deficiency of the activity of the pyrimidine pathway enzyme uridine 5&apos;-monophosphate (UMP) synthase. Clinical manifestations include growth retardation, anemia, and increased excretion of orotic acid in the urine.</NCI_Definition>
        <ID rdf:datatype="&xsd;string">C98944</ID>
        <NCI_PT rdf:datatype="&xsd;string">Hereditary Orotic Aciduria</NCI_PT>
