        <SYN rdf:datatype="&xsd;string"></SYN>
        <NCI_Definition rdf:datatype="&xsd;string">A severe autosomal dominant inherited disorder caused by mutations in the FGFR3 gene. It is characterized by multiple skeletal abnormalities, including extremely short limbs. It results in the death of the neonate.</NCI_Definition>
